"```sql\nSELECT e.expense_id, e.approved\nFROM expense e\nJOIN budget b ON e.link_to_budget = b.budget_id\nJOIN event ev ON b.link_to_event = ev.event_id\nWHERE ev.event_name = 'October Meeting' AND ev.event_date = '2019-10-08';\n```\n\nThis SQL query retrieves the `expense_id` and `approved` status of each expense related to the \"October Meeting\" event that took place on October 8, 2019. It joins the `expense`, `budget`, and `event` tables to filter the expenses associated with the specified event."